	<div id="post-2441475">
		<h1 class="entry-title">Bills hiring former Eagles wideout Chad&nbsp;Hall</h1>
	<div class="post-info">
	Posted by Darin Gantt on February 7, 2017, 11:44 AM EST</div>
	<div class="post-body clearfix">
		<span class="enclosure" style="width:250px;"><img width="250" height="166" src="https://nbcprofootballtalk.files.wordpress.com/2012/08/610x-13.jpg?w=250" class="featured-image wp-post-image" alt="Chad Hall" srcset="https://nbcprofootballtalk.files.wordpress.com/2012/08/610x-13.jpg?w=250 250w, https://nbcprofootballtalk.files.wordpress.com/2012/08/610x-13.jpg?w=500 500w, https://nbcprofootballtalk.files.wordpress.com/2012/08/610x-13.jpg?w=200 200w, https://nbcprofootballtalk.files.wordpress.com/2012/08/610x-13.jpg?w=320 320w" sizes="(max-width: 250px) 100vw, 250px" data-attachment-id="1087081" data-permalink="http://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2012/08/02/thursday-morning-one-liners-172/chad-hall/" data-orig-file="https://nbcprofootballtalk.files.wordpress.com/2012/08/610x-13.jpg" data-orig-size="610,406" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;AP&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Philadelphia Eagles wide receiver Chad Hall, right, has his head shaved by a member of the military to get his teammates to pledge money to the Wounded Warrior Project, after the team&#039;s NFL football training camp at Lehigh University in Bethlehem, Pa, Wednesday, Aug. 1, 2012. (AP Photo\/Rich Schultz)&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1343840852&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Chad Hall&quot;}" data-image-title="Chad Hall" data-image-description="&lt;p&gt;Philadelphia Eagles wide receiver Chad Hall, right, has his head shaved by a member of the military to get his teammates to pledge money to the Wounded Warrior Project, after the team&#8217;s NFL football training camp at Lehigh University in Bethlehem, Pa, Wednesday, Aug. 1, 2012. (AP Photo/Rich Schultz)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://nbcprofootballtalk.files.wordpress.com/2012/08/610x-13.jpg?w=320" data-large-file="https://nbcprofootballtalk.files.wordpress.com/2012/08/610x-13.jpg?w=610" /> <span class="caption">AP</span></span><p>Sean McDermott finally got a chance to be a head coach, so he&#8217;s going to help some other guys he know get a break in the business.</p>
<p>According to Albert Breer of TheMMQB.com, the Bills are <a href="https://twitter.com/AlbertBreer/status/828996773033234433">hiring</a> former NFL wide receiver/return man Chad Hall as a coaching assistant.</p>
<p>Hall was with the Eagles in 2010 when McDermott was on staff there, after making the team as an undrafted rookie from Air Force (after he served his service commitment).</p>
<p>Hall also spent some time with the 49ers, Chiefs, and Jaguars.</p>
